rComments: Honestly Rami is the single best Comp. Eng. professor at uOttawa. He is passionate about what he teaches, is incredibly knowledgeable, and can confer that knowledge in an effective and succinct way. He makes you work hard (esp. CEG3155), but by the time you're done you will be a very skilled engineer if you put in the work.

Rami is an incredible professor, the labs are kinda tough and you're going to have to put in a lot of work if you want to actually complete them. My advice would be to attend the lectures live because he's a very interactive professor and he definitely remembers names. If you do well in CEG3155 with him then CEG3156 will be a lot less work.

Professor Rami is really the type of professor who will make you love Computer Engineering. Although this is an advanced computer system design course, he made it well-organized and conveyed the subject matters clearly. If you want to learn a lot about Computer Engineering and help with your career as a Computer Engineer, definitely take him!

CEG 3155 will be a rough ride, this is the first thing you will hear when entering his lectures. Since he teaches 3155 and 3156 in sequence, he will shift most workload to 3155 . If you want this course to be easy, learn VHDL before you need to work with it. The labs are the only challenges,and the TAs will give you most marks for right logics.

He's a ok prof but the course is hard and also suffers from the fact that there is quizzes, labs, assignments, a final project and a midterm. This class will literally take up all your time and if you don't stay ahead you'll fall behind easily.

Rami Abielmona is a fantastic professor. He gives great concise lectures and is very forgiving on marking. As long as you pay a bit of attention, you will easily pass the course and learn a lot with his teaching.

Great prof, truly an understanding and caring prof. I found the quizzes, assignments and exams to be very fair and he is not a harsh marker like several of the other profs. I thought I would fail but ended up surprised at my marks.

expects way too much from his students. The midterm was ridiculously hard and very long. The average for the midterm was so horrible, he had to bell curve it. Labs were extremely hard (although TA was an easy marker). Hate the fact that you need a 50% on the exam to pass the class regardless of your mark.

The prof is fine and tries to help explain concepts but this course is very hard. The fact that both the Midterm and Final had to be bell-curved shows just how hard this course is. Doesn't help that you have to get 50% on the Final to pass the course no matter your other grades. The labs were also not easy and 2 stations had broken equipment.
The course material might not be everyone's favourite (and the labs are rough) but he's a solid lecturer. His lectures are filled with useful info and make you want to actually pay attention.
Excellent teacher!
100% would take again! Rami is a great resource. He'd stop and answer any of my questions. He's not your typical boring prof, the man is a weapon.
Good Prof!

Great prof. Lectures are interesting and I genuinely wanted to go to class. Convey the material very well. Would take class with him again. His tests are not impossible, however they are not a walk in the park.

I've been in OttawaU for 4 years now... and hands down, Dr. Rami is one of the most inspirational men i've ever meet.  Absolutely brilliant - from his style of teaching to his genuine character.  I would STRONGLY recommend him to any of my friends - he's not a tough grader, just read your material like any other student
He is the best professor EVER !!! the best part his feedback and his experience of University.

Dr. Abielmona is an excellent lecturer. If you skip the lectures or show up expecting to passively absorb information, then you will not be successful. His lectures are challenging and interesting. It was so refreshing to have a professor who is both knowledgeable and a strong public speaker.  My only complaint is the labs. They're a pain.

He talks really fast. Rerally go to lectures, study at home is enough. This prof is really nice, easy marker, tests are similar with previous ones; study all of them. Study is all you need, A is garanteed.

Great prof, he's very enthusiastic and clear, although he teaches pretty quickly.  Is always happy to answer questions and explain concepts after class.  However, he crams a LOT of info into one class (3-hour lectures go right to the end) and it's hard to keep focused on it after an hour or so - his slides are often overflowing with info.

he's a good prof and knows his stuff very well. he also is funny at times and you can tell he loves what hes doing. however, the 3h lectures feel way longer than they truly are because he crams too much information in one period.  like his powerpoint slides are legit overflowing with info (and a lot of it isnt even on the tests).
he's the best teacher i ever had !!  Like Seriously ...  he makes everything more interesting.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: He is good professor, has a lot of knowledge and is proud of it. speaks fast but if you are attentive then its okay.

He is definitely very knowledgeable in this subject, thus expects a lot from you. Is rude sometimes but always helps you when you ask. The course content was huge, there was a project, tests, midterm and final exam too. Still a good teacher but not the best.

Excellent professor ! Definitely knows his stuff. He is fair, professional, and understanding. I really can say I have learned a lot from him even though I am not very interested in his field. Hard to find a prof like him these days.
A lot of slides. Knows his stuff. Course wasn't too bad. I'd take it again with him.

Very good prof even though he talks quite FAST. More importantly (unlike many ENG prof), he KNOWS his stuff as if he was born with a computer in his brain. Also his not a tough grader, overall an excellent teacher.

One of the best Profs I've ever had at the University of Ottawa. Very passionate about the material and is able to convey it clearly to his students. Everything is straightforward if you pay attention to the lectures. Definitely a Prof worth changing sections for.

One of the best prof. Teaches you to learn for the future, not for exam. Speaks very very fast. Every word is important and worth focusing for. Lots of homework. Not much hint for exam. Focus in class, you'll be ready for exam. Give quizzes for you to be ever ready. Lenient in marking.

He's a great professor and I think he's an easy marker. I skipped classes many times after the midterm. Basically, I learnt lots of stuff from my friend who attended his class all the time. Finally, my friend got A+ and I got A-. I'm pretty sure you won't regret if you choose him as your professor.
the best prof. so far
Very clear when explaining the concepts but also adds in a bit of humour once in a while to keep us from getting bored. My straight male friend also thinks he's cute.

If you land on having this man as your professor, you should consider yourself extremely lucky! Hands down one of the best professors I have come across at the University of Ottawa. Very approachable, knows his material inside-out and conveys it in extremely good manner. You will learn A LOT in his class. Simply put: brilliant, brilliant man!
in my four years of schooling, this prof was most definitely the smartest and most intriguing one of them all! I hope you all get him as a prof!!
The Best Professor I have had.
The best teacher i had so far.
respect.

I think that he lives inside the computer. He inspired me to love Computer Engineering again.
AMAZING TA, knows his stuff inside out!
Definitively the best teacher at the University of Ottawa!
Same comments as everyone else.  Very approachable and an excellent teacher - knows his subject inside out.
hey malmsteen of engineering, learn to speak english
Rami I proudly award you the title: WILHELM HEINRICH HERTZ
This man deserves admission into MIT or Berkeley, but he is doing his university a great favour by staying there.
We learned more in one class with Rami than the previous two years of teaching from Aldeher(sp?)

Absolutely the best teacher ever. This guy is a genius. He has no trouble taking all that intelligence and explaining things so the rest of us understand.  I hope Rami pursues a future in the academia world, he's a great asset to the school and students.
So annoying!

This is the only class I've ever taken where when he was finished his last lecture the entire class gave him a standing ovation.  He deserved it!  If hes your prof congratulations.
Yngwie Malmsteen of computer engineering. The evolution has just began.

Unbelievable prof. If you get the chance to be his student use it!  You will learn everything that you have not learned from other profs.  I learned more in his class than all other classes combined!~
Simply stated, the best prof in Ottawa U.
